				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/novaedearx" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1310897); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1310897&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250341" alt="NovaeDeArx" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1310897)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/novaedearx" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1310897); return false;" >NovaeDeArx</a></span> <span class="odate time_1435344018 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">26 Jun 2015 18:40</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2325680">
									

<p>Props for doing your research - most people (well, most Americans anyway) don't know that if America hadn't nuked Japan, Russia would have rolled over the top of them in roughly 2-6 weeks. (Or that the Russians' actions trying to get there quickly are why South Korea <em>really</em> doesn't like communists, but that's not related to the story)</p>
<p>Anyway, this was fantastically written; you've done a great job of capturing the &quot;feel&quot; of war, both how it feels during and after, and the characterization is well-done also. You should definitely finish this.</p>

							</div>

								
					
