								<div class="title" id="post-title-3577377">
																		I&#039;ll be replying to the original Author Post for updates from here on out, I think.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-macleod" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1922529); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1922529&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250341" alt="Agent MacLeod" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1922529)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-macleod" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1922529); return false;" >Agent MacLeod</a></span> <span class="odate time_1503564476 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Aug 2017 08:47</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3577377">
									

<p>This story is something of a source of shame for me because of how much it has stagnated, incomplete. I hadn't initially intended for it to be this monolithic, multi-chapter novella that it's become. And, when I decided on the route I did, I hadn't anticipated that it'd stagnate for so long. I ran headlong into writer's block that, for this particular story, persists. Maybe I was too ambitious, I don't know. I do that sometimes.</p>
<p>However, I knew how this story was going to end fairly early into its expansion from its initial chapter into what it is set to become. One way I work around writer's block is to chip away at different stories from the one that's got me stumped. It just so happens that I finished the epilogue to this story a long time ago. It's been sitting in my sandbox in its current form for a very long time.</p>
<p>Since it's been two years since I updated, I figured I might as well give you guys something to show that I haven't forgotten, that I'm still trying to work out the kinks.</p>
<p>Sorry this has been delayed so long. I hope y'all enjoy what's here, and I hope I can deliver the rest sometime relatively soon.</p>

							</div>

								
