			<div class="content" id="post-content-2326913">
									

<p>According to Wikipedia, the DShK is 1.6 meters long. (I'm not gonna bother mentioning weight, because, for these folks, it wouldn't be an issue.) Even sawing off the barrel would still leave it big and cumbersome. A beefed-up AK, on the other hand, can be significantly smaller, and easier to move when you're moving through, say, enemy bunker complexes, which are guaranteed to be CQB situations.</p>
<p>Plus, the AK is probably the most reliable weapons system ever constructed, so why not use it for the end of the world? That was my reasoning, anyway.</p>

